				\begin{document}$$Event (var1,\,var2,\,varn)|conditionaction$$\end{document} Here E is an event name, and the variables var1, var2, etc denote the arguments of this event. The expression condition should evaluate to a boolean value, and can make use of common arithmetic and relational operators. It involves the variables in V, the event arguments, and the distinguished variable state that refers to the current control state of the EFSA.
